0.8
+ Try to make zooming smoother (is this even possible with pygtk?)
+ Documentation
+ Resize, rotate, crop, and save (luzi)
	- Saving: jpeg/png, quality, transparency (for png) - pixbuf.save()
		- File > Save, File > Save As...
	- Cropping: pixbuf.copy_area()
		- Edit > Crop...
	- Resizing: same as zooming..
		- Edit > Resize...
	- Rotating/Flipping: done
	- Pref: Auto-saving - No, yes, prompt
		- Edit > Prefs > Behavior
+ Side/bottom pane for thumbnails of all images in list (use .thumbnails?)

Future
+ Bookmarks (Bookmark Image, Bookmark List, Manage (to create files))?
